cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with text detection in natural scene images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method that incorporates a pyramid pooling module, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also involves text recognition, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations, which can be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
